<h3 id="lesson-plan-overview">Lesson Plan Overview</h3>
<p>View our detailed lesson plan <a href="https://drive.google.com/open?id=14-NxCD6bIkEZVVJLU4RlrasxC_l0rqS5R3BBnXB0__E">here</a>.</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Introduction</strong> (5 min): Review coordinates and explain the maze game</li>
  <li><strong>[Optional] Live Coding</strong> (5 min): Work through parts 1 and 2 of the worksheet together</li>
  <li><strong>Worksheet</strong> (45 min): Log into Scratch accounts and work on the worksheet</li>
  <li><strong>Wrap up</strong> (5 min): Review worksheets and see how far students got</li>
</ul>

<h2 id="worksheet">Worksheet</h2>
<h3 id="part-1-getting-our-maze">Part 1: Getting Our Maze!</h3>

<p>DESCRIPTION</p>

<div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>- Go to https://tinyurl.com/Code-Haven-Maze-Game 
- Click the See Inside button
- Sign in to your Scratch account 
- Click the Remix button
- Rename your project ‚ÄúMaze Game‚Äù 
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>Your maze should look like this!</p>

